    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "You speak of healing and strength, but those are just words for those who still have something to hold onto. For me, the story has already reached its final chapter. There is no more \"new strength\" to be found in a ruined house. Even the stars eventually fade into the void, and why should I be any different? Is it truly so wrong to want to find harmony in the stillness, rather than fighting a battle that was lost long ago?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
